<paragraph blockId="23.[189,630,1334,1361]" box="[189,630,1334,1361]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
LENGTH. Body 
<quantity box="[362,455,1334,1361]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
, wing 
<quantity box="[532,625,1334,1361]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1399,1531]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
HEAD (
<figureCitation box="[272,370,1399,1425]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,518,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Megatrigon spp., head, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E–F. M.natalensissp. nov.(arrow =postocellarspot)(♁).G.M.sexmaculatus sp. nov.(♁).H. M.apiformis sp. nov. (♁). I. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). J. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). K. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). L. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). M. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀). Symbol: x = postocellar spot." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849882" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849882/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Figs 2H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[385,421,1399,1425]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">3G</figureCitation>
). Distance between eyes, 0.16–0.17 × width of head; post-ocular orbit wider, the width of post-ocular orbit dorsally 0.13–0.14 as wide as head; ocellar triangle isosceles, without median longitudinal groove; postpedicel (
<figureCitation box="[584,674,1470,1496]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[188,231,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1359,267,1781]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Megatrigon spp., left antenna, lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. (♁). B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. (♁). C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. (♁). D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). E. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. (♁). G. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. (♁). I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. (♁). J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁). K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. (♁). L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov. (♁). M. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♀)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849886" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849886/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
) almost rounded, 1.2–1.3 × as long as deep, 1.6–1.7 × as long as pedicel; supra-alar setae yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1147,1570,1597]" box="[189,1147,1570,1597]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
THORAX (
<figureCitation box="[297,389,1570,1597]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[291,1281,1100,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[291,1281,1100,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Megatrigon spp., mesoscutum, dorsal view. A. Megatrigon magnicornis sp. nov. (♁). B. M. natalensis sp. nov. (♁). C. M. apiformis sp. nov. (♁). D. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. (♁)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849890" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849890/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Microtrichia on mediotergite covered about one third of width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1250,1636,1663]" box="[189,1250,1636,1663]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
WING (
<figureCitation box="[270,360,1636,1663]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1494,1520]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,610,1456]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[189,1399,609,1457]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 5. Megatrigon spp., right wing, ♁. A. Megatrigon apiformis sp. nov. B. M. cooksoni sp. nov. C. M. tabanoides sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849894" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849894/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Setae on costagium yellow; wing veins mostly yellow, but darker distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1701,1798]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
LEGS. Setae on legs yellow; only apex of pro- and mesofemur lighter, not also the base; of tarsi, only tarsomere 1 of metaleg darkened dorsally; microtrichia on metatibia dorsally relatively short like in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Doczkal &amp; Radenković &amp; Lyneborg &amp; Pape" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Megatrigon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argenteus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">M. argenteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[311,441,1772,1798]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1837,2004]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
ABDOMEN (
<figureCitation box="[315,407,1837,1864]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1862,1888]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1399,265,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 7. Megatrigon spp., abdomen, dorsal view, ♁. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. jacobi (Hervé-Bazin, 1913) comb. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849902/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
). Relatively narrow, tergite 2 is 1.8 × and tergite 3 is 2 × as wide as long; tergites with a golden lustre, long, dense, golden setose; tergites 2–4 with transversal, yellow-white microtrichiose fasciae connected in the middle; fasciae on tergites 2+3 oblique and reaching lateral margins, tergite 4 with horizontal fasciae, widely separated from lateral margin; tergite 4 with wide microtrichiose posterior margin and one or two pairs of depressions; indistinct white microtrichia present anteromedially on
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1398,267,329]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
tergites 2–4, more developed on tergite 2, but on tergites 3+4 connected with fasciae along the median line. Male genitalia in 
<figureCitation box="[454,564,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[189,232,1825,1851]" captionTargetBox="[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[216,1374,263,1796]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 10. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, epandrium, left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. Megatrigon sp. from sexfasciatus group. M. M. nivalis. Symbols: x = ventral margin of median surstyle; y = posterior surstyle; z = cercus; w = subepandrial sclerite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849914/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Figs 10G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[577,629,303,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1758,1784]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[189,1399,340,1716]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium (A–M) and phallus (N), left lateral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. sexmaculatus sp. nov. G. M. apiformis sp. nov. H. M. cooksoni sp. nov. I. M. immaculatus sp. nov. J. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. K. M. tabanoides sp. nov. L. M. sp. from sexfasciatus group. M–N. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = hamus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849918" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849918/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">11G</figureCitation>
, 
<specimenCount box="[641,692,303,329]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="generic">
<figureCitation box="[641,688,303,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[189,232,1794,1820]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[189,1399,442,1753]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 12. Megatrigon spp., ♁ terminalia, hypandrium, ventral view. A. Megatrigon argenteus (Walker, 1852) comb. nov. B. M. argentifrons sp. nov. C. M. argentimaculatus sp. nov. D. M. magnicornis sp. nov. E. M. natalensis sp. nov. F. M. apiformis sp. nov. G. M. cooksoni sp. nov. H. M. immaculatus sp. nov. I. M. ochreatus (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. J. M. tabanoides sp. nov. K. Megatrigon sp. from the sexfasciatus group. L. M. nivalis (Hull, 1964) comb. nov. Symbol: x = lateral ‘shoulders’." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3849922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3849922/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">12F</figureCitation>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
